PURPOSE

Stable, public information about Loon, Chickadee, Blue Jay, and the full Loon Lounge estate. Use these facts for booking questions, property comparisons, amenities, accessibility, and guest fit.

This file contains facts, not agent behavior instructions. The system prompt controls privacy, booking intake, tone, and escalation.

PRIVACY BOUNDARY

This public file contains no street address, access code, Wi-Fi password, lockbox information, or private host or staff phone number. The public voice agent must never provide those details. Confirmed guests receive arrival information separately.

OVERVIEW

The Loon Lounge is a group of three family-owned lakefront vacation homes on Green Lake in Dedham, Maine: Loon, Chickadee, and Blue Jay. Guests may book one home or all three as the Estate. Acadia National Park and Bar Harbor are approximately 45 minutes away before summer traffic and parking delays. Ellsworth is about 20 minutes away and Bangor about 30 minutes away.

EXACT CAPACITIES

- Blue Jay: four bedrooms; sleeps 8 in beds; 8 is the maximum.
- Chickadee: four bedrooms; sleeps 8 in beds; 8 is the maximum.
- Loon main house: four bedrooms; sleeps 8 in beds.
- Loon with the walk-out apartment: sleeps 11 in beds and up to 15 only when both sleeper sofas are used.
- Estate: 12 bedrooms and three kitchens; sleeps 27 in beds and up to 31 only when Loon's sleeper sofas are used.

Never estimate above these capacities or imply that a larger group will fit.

LOON

Loon is the largest of the three homes. The main house has four bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms and sleeps 8 in beds.

Main-house bedrooms:
- Upstairs vaulted king bedroom with a lake view; a portable crib is available.
- Upstairs queen bedroom with a lake view.
- Upstairs full bedroom.
- The three upstairs bedrooms share one bathroom with a double vanity and shower/tub combination.
- Ground-floor king suite with a private sunroom and en-suite bathroom.
- A separate ground-floor half-bath serves guests.

The main entrance is level. The kitchen door, ground-floor bathroom, and ground-floor king suite can be reached without stairs.

The separate walk-out apartment has its own entrance, lake view, full bathroom, kitchenette, one four-poster queen bed, one single bed, one full sleeper sofa, and one queen sleeper sofa. It is an open living and sleeping space rather than a set of private bedrooms. The apartment adds three regular beds, bringing Loon to 11 guests in beds, and the two sleeper sofas bring the maximum to 15. The apartment is down a steep hill from the main house.

Loon has panoramic lake views from every bedroom and from the apartment. It is the only house with its own private beach and the property's only dock. When Loon is booked separately, Loon guests have exclusive use of that beach and dock. When the full Estate is booked, the Estate group has access to them. Loon also has a deck, patio, gas grill, outdoor dining area, and fire pit. Loon does not have a screened porch.

Loon cleaning fee: $350 for every booking configuration, including bookings with the walk-out apartment.

CHICKADEE

Chickadee has four bedrooms and 3.5 bathrooms and sleeps a maximum of 8 in beds.

Bedrooms:
- Main-floor king bedroom with a lake view and en-suite bathroom.
- Upstairs king bedroom with a lake view, a crib for one small child, and an en-suite bathroom with a shower/tub combination.
- Upstairs queen bedroom.
- Upstairs twin bedroom with two twin beds.
- The queen and twin bedrooms share a Jack-and-Jill bathroom.

Chickadee has a step-free main floor from its accessible parking space along a lit path and ramp to the guest entrance, kitchen, living space, and main-floor king suite. The ramped guest entrance is wider than 81 centimeters, and interior doorways are 32 inches wide. The main-floor en-suite has a low-profile shower with a 2-inch threshold; it is not a roll-in shower. There are grab bars at the toilet and shower and wheelchair turning space in the bathroom.

The other three bedrooms require stairs. The beach is down a steeper hill and is not step-free.

Chickadee has a screened porch overlooking the lake, plus a deck, gas grill, outdoor dining area, and fire pit. Its beach is shared only with Blue Jay.

Chickadee cleaning fee: $300.

BLUE JAY

Blue Jay has four bedrooms and two full bathrooms and sleeps a maximum of 8 in beds. All four bedrooms are upstairs and require stairs.

Bedrooms:
- Two queen bedrooms with lake views.
- Two bedrooms with full beds.
- One full bathroom is upstairs and one is on the ground floor; the four bedrooms share these bathrooms.

Blue Jay has floor-to-ceiling lake views from the open living and kitchen space and a screened porch overlooking the water. It also has a gas grill, outdoor dining area, and fire pit. Its beach is a few steps from the house and is shared only with Chickadee.

Blue Jay cleaning fee: $275.

THE ESTATE

The Estate is all three neighboring homes rented to one group. It provides 12 bedrooms, three kitchens, both beaches, access to the one dock at Loon, two screened porches, three fire pits, and several indoor and outdoor gathering spaces.

The Estate sleeps 27 guests in beds or up to 31 only when Loon's sleeper sofas are used. Two homes, Loon and Chickadee, have ground-floor king bedrooms. Weddings, events, retreats, commercial activity, and other special uses require advance written approval and may have separate terms, fees, and occupancy limits.

SHARED AMENITIES AND EQUIPMENT

- Fast fiber Wi-Fi is available in all three homes. Network names and passwords are private arrival information and are not in this document.
- There are no televisions, by design.
- Three kayaks, two paddleboards, and one canoe are shared among the three homes unless the Estate is booked by one group.
- Life jackets are available in several sizes. Families should bring a properly fitted life jacket for any child who needs a specific size.
- Every home has blackout shades, board games, and puzzles.
- Each home has a gas grill, fire pit, and outdoor dining space.
- Each home has a washer, dryer, and laundry detergent available at no charge.
- Each kitchen has a drip coffee maker, coffee filters, kettle, toaster, and microwave.
- There is no hammock.

HEAT, COOLING, POWER, AND SEASONS

All three homes are heated, winterized, plowed, and available for winter stays. Four-wheel drive or all-wheel drive is recommended in winter. Weather does not qualify a booking for a refund.

There is no air conditioning. Chickadee has ample fans. Loon and Blue Jay have portable fans in the closets. Cross-ventilation through open windows works well on hot days. In summer, mosquitoes can be small enough to get through screens, so keeping windows closed when lights are on at night can help keep them outside.

The property has a backup generator for power outages. Emergency flashlights are stored near the entry of each house, and every kitchen has a fire extinguisher.

PARKING

Each house has one designated parking space directly in front of it. Chickadee's designated space is accessible. Additional vehicles must use the overflow parking area on the right side of the road before the turn into the property driveway. Vehicles must not block the driveway or another home's space.

Vehicles and trailers must never drive over the grounds because septic and gas tanks and lines are buried there.

BOATS AND WATER ACCESS

Guests may bring or rent a boat but must tell the team in advance. Boats cannot be launched from the property; use a public ramp nearby.

Trailers and vehicles may not cross the property. Boats must stay on the assigned mooring and may use the dock only for loading and unloading. Do not leave a boat tied to the dock overnight because waves can be strong and the dock is not intended for overnight boat storage.

The property has no lifeguard or swim ropes. Children must be supervised around the lake. A properly fitted life jacket is required for every paddler.

CORE POLICIES

- Check-in is at 4:00 p.m.; check-out is at 10:00 a.m.
- Quiet hours are 10:00 p.m. to 7:00 a.m.
- Children are welcome and must be supervised around the lake.
- No pets or animals are permitted because of allergies. Service-animal situations must be routed to a member of the team for individual follow-up.
- No smoking or vaping inside any building.
- Exterior cameras are present at all three homes; there are no interior cameras.
- The homes use septic systems. Flush only toilet paper and never flush wipes, including products labeled flushable.

BOOKING-FIT FACTS

- For a private beach and dock: recommend Loon.
- For the clearest step-free main-floor option and an accessible king suite: recommend Chickadee, using the exact measurements and shower description above.
- For a classic lake-house layout, screened porch, and shared beach: recommend Blue Jay, while making clear that every bedroom is upstairs.
- For more guests than one home can accommodate: offer another single home only if its exact capacity fits, two neighboring homes, or the Estate.
- Blue Jay and Chickadee are next to each other and share a beach, making them a practical two-house combination.

